          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄγαλμα</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγάλλομαι</span>): anything in which one takes
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">delight</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pride</span>, a ‘treasure,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 4.144</span></i>; applied to votive offerings,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 3.274</span></i>; a sacrificial victim,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 3.438</span></i>; horses, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.602</span></i>; personal adornments, <i><span class="en">Od. 18.300</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
